\end{aligned}
$$
where $\operatorname{concat}\left(s_{t-1}, x_{t}\right)$ is a vector of length $m+d$ obtained by concatenating $s_{t-1}$ and $x_{t}$, so $W^{s s x}$ has dimensions $m \times(m+d)$.
